# Toasts: `goey-toast`

**Always use [goey-toast](https://www.npmjs.com/package/goey-toast)** for toast notifications in this project (morphing / “gooey” toasts). Do **not** add alternate toast libraries unless explicitly requested.

- **Package:** `npm install goey-toast`
- **Peers:** `react`, `react-dom`, `framer-motion` (ensure installed)

## Setup

1. **Import styles once** (required — toasts use Sonner `unstyled`; blob UI lives in CSS):

   ```css
   /* e.g. app/globals.css */
   @import "goey-toast/styles.css";
   ```

   Without this, toasts look broken / unstyled. DevTools will warn: `[gooey-toast] Styles not found`.

2. Render **`GooeyToaster`** once near the app root (e.g. inside a client `Providers` in `layout.tsx`), with desired **`position`**, **`theme`**, **`preset`**, **`offset`**, etc.

3. Call **`gooeyToast`** from **`goey-toast`** only in **client** code.

```tsx
import { GooeyToaster, gooeyToast } from "goey-toast";

// root: <GooeyToaster position="bottom-right" theme="light" preset="smooth" />
// client: gooeyToast.success("Saved!");
```

Optional shadcn-style wrapper: `npx shadcn@latest add https://goey-toast.vercel.app/r/goey-toaster.json` then import from `@/components/ui/goey-toaster`.

## API surface to prefer

Use the **right variant** for context:

| Situation | Call |
|-----------|------|
| Neutral | `gooeyToast("…")` |
| OK / confirm | `gooeyToast.success("…", { description?: … })` |
| Failure | `gooeyToast.error("…", { description?: … })` |
| Caution | `gooeyToast.warning("…", { description?: … })` |
| Informational | `gooeyToast.info("…", { description?: … })` |
| Async flow | `gooeyToast.promise(promise, { loading, success, error, description?: { success, error }, action?: … })` |

**Descriptions:** string or `ReactNode` for richer bodies.

**Actions:** `{ label, onClick, successLabel? }` for morph-back pill after click.

**Timing:** per-toast `duration` (ms); global default on `<GooeyToaster duration={…} />`.

**Styling:** `fillColor`, `borderColor`, `borderWidth`, `classNames: { wrapper, content, header, title, icon, description, actionWrapper, actionButton }`.

**Motion:** per-toast or global `spring`, `bounce`, `preset` (`smooth` | `bouncy` | `subtle` | `snappy`).

**Programmatic:** `gooeyToast.dismiss(id?)`, `gooeyToast.dismiss({ type: "error" })`, `gooeyToast.update(id, { title, description, type, action })`.

**Lifecycle:** `onDismiss`, `onAutoClose` when needed.

## Conventions for this codebase

- Prefer **`gooeyToast.success` / `error` / `warning` / `info`** for POS flows (payment, cart, QR orders, kitchen handoff).
- Use **`gooeyToast.promise`** for saves, uploads, or API calls that resolve/reject.
- Use **descriptions** for user-facing detail; keep titles short.
- Match **`theme`** to the surrounding UI (`light` / `dark`) when mounting `GooeyToaster`.
- **Client-only:** only call `gooeyToast` from client components or effects (not during RSC render).
